# Environment variables

# ======================================================================
# Custom Key-Based Configuration (Recommended for shared/public deployments)
# ======================================================================
# This allows you to pre-configure Google Drive settings that are loaded via URL
# Usage: Add ?key=YOUR_KEY to the URL
# Example: https://yourapp.com/?key=myevent
#
# Format: VITE_CONFIG_[KEY_NAME]=enabled,clientId,folderId
# The key is stored in sessionStorage and destroyed when a new session with the same URL starts

# Example configurations:
# VITE_CONFIG_MYEVENT=true,123456789-abcdefg.apps.googleusercontent.com,1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0j
# VITE_CONFIG_WEDDING=true,987654321-xyz.apps.googleusercontent.com,
# VITE_CONFIG_BIRTHDAY=false,,

# ======================================================================
# Manual Configuration (For personal use or development)
# ======================================================================
# Users can manually configure Google Drive settings via the Settings UI
# These are stored in localStorage and persist across sessions

# ======================================================================
# Priority Order:
# 1. URL key-based config (if ?key=VALUE is present)
# 2. Manual Settings UI config (stored in localStorage)
# ======================================================================
